cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.OH, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the problem of recovering spatial and temporal information from sparse photon counts, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of ConvNet-based schemes, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of noise reduction, which is relevant to optimization and control (cs.OH).
